    <title>Create Scorecards using the Pivot Table app</title>
    <para><emphasis><emphasis role="bold">Scorecards definition:</emphasis> In public health
        settings such as Ministries of Health, scorecards offer a useful and standardized method for combining related indicators into one table. A scorecard gives an overall view of the performance of a health program such as a
        vaccination program, highlighting successes, weaknesses, and areas for improvement
            Here's what a typical  scorecard looks like:</emphasis>  
        <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_result.png"
                        align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot></para>
    <para><emphasis>This tutorial explains how to create a scorecard in the DHIS2 Pivot Table app. There are several advantages to using the Pivot Table to create a scorecard, such as:</emphasis></para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para><emphasis>You can save the scorecard on the dashboard and use it
                    offline.</emphasis></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><emphasis>You can share the scorecard with other DHIS2 users.</emphasis></para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para><emphasis>Let's get started!</emphasis></para>
    <section><title>Create a legend for your scorecard</title>
        <para>First, we’ll create a 3-color “traffic light” legend for the scorecard. With three
            basic colors, the scorecard is easy to scan and easy to understand.</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem><para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app. Click the menu in the top right
                    corner and select Maintenance from the list of apps. You can also type the first
                    letters of the word maintenance in the search field to find the app.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_app.png"
                                    align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>In the Maintenance app, scroll to the bottom of the page right down to the <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> section.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Legend</emphasis> and click the <emphasis role="bold"
            >+</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_legend.png"
                            align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot></para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Legend Management</emphasis> page, scroll to the bottom of the
            page and create a new legend by clicking the blue + button.<screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_addbtn.png"
                            align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot></para></listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter a name for the legend such as “Traffic Light”, a start value and an end
                    value in the fields. The values you enter here depend on the performance ratings
                    you wish to set for the scorecard.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Change <emphasis role="bold">Number of legend items</emphasis> to 3 to obtain
                    three colors in the scorecard. To change the legend item colors, click the blue
                    + button and then edit the colors.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_maintenance_legend_color.png"
                                    align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
    </itemizedlist></section>

    <section><title>Create a scorecard in the Pivot Table app</title>
        <para></para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem><para>Open the Pivot Table app from the top right menu of the dashboard. You can also enter the first letters of Pivot Table in the search field.</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Go to the <emphasis role="bold">Data</emphasis> menu in the pane on the left side and select
                        <emphasis role="bold">Indicators</emphasis> in the list.</para></listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Indicator group</emphasis> such as “ANC” from
                    the second list.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem><para>Using the arrows, select the type of indicators you want to see in your scorecard.<screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_indicators.png"
                            align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot></para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>. This button is in the menu at the top of the
                    workspace</para></listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Periods</emphasis> and select a period for which
                    you want to display data. In this “traffic light” example, we’ll go to the
                    relative period section, where the checkboxes are. In <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Quarters</emphasis>, select <emphasis role="bold">This quarter
                    </emphasis>and <emphasis role="bold">Last quarter</emphasis>. Clear any other
                    checkboxes and click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_period.png"
                                    align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">Organisation Units</emphasis> in the same left
                    side pane, and click the arrow next to the gear icon.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Select levels</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_orgunit_level.png"
                                align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">District</emphasis> from the list next to the
                    gear. Click <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.<screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="resources/images/tutorials/scorecards_pivot_orgunit_level2.png"
                                    align="left" width="90%" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist><para>As you can see, the scorecard is starting to take shape in the workspace. Now it’s time to fine-tune the look and feel.</para></section>

